research/audit-evidence-base.md-38-
research/audit-evidence-base.md-39-### Brazil — TCU and CGU (the strongest systematic series)
research/audit-evidence-base.md-40-
research/audit-evidence-base.md:41:- **[S→P queue]** TCU, *Diagnóstico de Obras Paralisadas* (operational audit and continuing panel, 2018-19 onward). Category: construction. Of ~21,000 federally funded works that should be in execution, **more than 8,600 (~41%) paralyzed or unfinished**, with R$8.2+ billion already invested in them. Informs: the reported-vs-real completion analogue for works — the single most direct calibration item for the construction arm's non-delivery share. <https://portal.tcu.gov.br/biblioteca-digital/auditoria-operacional-sobre-obras-paralisadas.htm>
research/audit-evidence-base.md-42-- **[P]** TCU, *Fiscobras 2023* (27th annual works-audit plan). Category: construction. 31 works audited, **21 (67%) with indications of grave irregularity**, R$17 B audited volume; risk-based selection declared (sampling bias toward suspect works — stated, not hidden). Informs: grave-deficiency detection rate in audited works; the annual series supports a multi-year band. <https://portal.tcu.gov.br/data/pages/8A81881F8A588DD8018B975855A6641E.htm>
research/audit-evidence-base.md:43:- **[S→P queue]** CGU, *Programa de Fiscalização em Entes Federativos* (municipal audit lotteries since 2003; >2,200 audits). Category: transfers/social programs. Reported synthesis: ~73% of audited administrations with irregularities; **~8.2% of federal transfers not applied as intended** — the direct candidate for the transfer arm's leakage level. Level figures are secondary until confirmed against the primary descriptive statistics in Avis, Ferraz and Finan (2018). <https://www.gov.br/cgu/pt-br/assuntos/auditoria-e-fiscalizacao/programa-de-fiscalizacao-em-entes-federativos>
research/audit-evidence-base.md-44-- **[P]** Ferraz and Finan (2011, AER); Avis, Ferraz and Finan (2018, JPE). Verified *effects*: reelection incentives reduce misappropriation by 27%; being audited reduces future corruption ~8% and raises subsequent legal action ~20%. Informs: the detection→deterrence elasticity (mechanism evidence, not a level).
