 401: ## E7 — Headline sensitivity under a calibrated status quo
 402: 
 403: Pre-registered in `research/e7-calibrated-baseline-design.md` before
 404: implementation, with a dated pre-run amendment governing parameter
 405: sourcing; raw output in `research/e7-raw-output.txt`. E7 answers A036 by
 406: running it: the E5 zero-control lower bound is joined by a **calibrated
 407: institutional arm S′** whose parameters come from the audit-institution
 408: evidence base (`research/audit-evidence-base.md`) per docs/105 — p = 0.35
 409: (the Chile CEA-CGR works-observation floor, mid of the 0.30-0.50 design
 410: band), a = 0.5 (payment-state retention practice), r = 0.3 (the ASF
 411: Mexico recovery band, denominator caveat declared), R = 0 (reputational
 412: memory is the instrument the status quo genuinely lacks), official
 413: completion still credited on paper certification for undetected
 414: diversion. The central planner's bandwidth scales as K = max(3,
 415: round(0.15·N_p)); scales N_p ∈ {10, 20, 40, 200}; coordinated
 416: common-mode signal bias β ∈ {0…0.40} on a favored set of 10% of
 417: projects. 20 seeded runs, matched portfolios and execution streams.
 418: 
 419: | arm (N_p = 200, β = 0) | V/budget | leak | visibility gap | sel(θ) |
 420: |---|---|---|---|---|
 421: | S — central fixed-K / zero-control | 0.374±0.061 | 0.324±0.072 | 0.293±0.066 | 0.138±0.071 |
 422: | S′ — central scaled-K / calibrated | 0.391±0.045 | 0.293±0.056 | 0.190±0.035 | 0.130±0.072 |
 423: | A1′ — central scaled-K / verified | 0.558±0.032 | 0.000±0.000 | 0.000±0.000 | 0.130±0.072 |
 424: | A3′ — distributed / calibrated | 0.608±0.068 | 0.293±0.079 | 0.190±0.051 | 0.764±0.023 |
 425: | A2 — distributed / verified | 0.859±0.023 | 0.000±0.000 | 0.000±0.000 | 0.764±0.023 |
 426: 
 427: Headline ratio at scale: **V(A2)/V(S′) = 2.224 [2.103, 2.346]** per-seed
 428: (ratio of means 2.197). At municipal scales under the post-hoc
 429: full-coverage planner (E7s below): ratio of means **1.387 (N_p = 10),
 430: 1.510 (N_p = 20), 1.627 (N_p = 40)**.
 431: 
 432: **Findings against the pre-registered predictions:**
 433: 
 434: 1. **Prediction 1 (multiplier falls below 1.5×) FAILED at scale, in the
 435:    informative direction.** The multiplier survives recalibration nearly
 436:    intact: 2.22 against the audit-calibrated baseline at N_p = 200. The
 437:    committed withdrawal condition (ratio near 1) is not triggered. At
 438:    municipal pilot scale, against the realistic full-coverage planner,
 439:    the ratio compresses to 1.39-1.63 — the prediction's spirit holds
 440:    there: at pilot scale the case rests on delivery and metering, not
 441:    selection.
 442: 2. **Prediction 2 FAILED informatively — and this is the experiment's
 443:    central finding: audit without memory deters nobody.** The calibrated
 444:    regime's IC threshold (0.2275) lies below every opportunist's cost
 445:    draw (c_eff ≥ 0.3), so no diversion is ever deterred: S′'s leak
 446:    (0.293) is statistically indistinguishable from zero-control on
 447:    matched portfolios, and the delivery effect measured against the
 448:    calibrated baseline (+0.167 [0.149, 0.186]) equals E5's against
 449:    zero-control (+0.168). What real-parameter detection buys is a
 450:    smaller lie, not more delivery: the visibility gap drops from 0.293
 451:    to 0.190. Sharpening rather than weakening the manuscript's claim:
 452:    the calibrated arm's leak lands inside the audit-anchored works band
 453:    (24-48%) — the model's leak mechanics, fed audit-anchored parameters,
 454:    reproduce the empirically documented band.
 455: 3. **Prediction 3 (municipal selection wash) MIXED.** Under the
 456:    committed 15%-bandwidth scaling the wash never occurs, because a
 457:    planner inspecting 15% of candidates is near-random at every scale
 458:    (sel(θ) 0.12-0.28) — a finding about that formalization, not about
 459:    municipal planners. Under the post-hoc full-coverage planner (the
 460:    realistic municipal comparator: K ≥ N_p) the wash holds exactly at
 461:    N_p ≤ 20 (sel 0.729 vs 0.725; 0.748 vs 0.749) and distributed pulls
 462:    ahead by N_p = 40 (0.624 vs 0.762).
 463: 4. **Prediction 4 (bias degrades linearly; crossover β\* in 0.25-0.35)
 464:    HELD against the competent comparator.** Distributed sel(θ) declines
 465:    near-linearly in β (0.764 → 0.558 at β = 40%); the favored set's
 466:    budget share rises monotonically (12% → 34% for 10% of projects).
 467:    Against the full-coverage municipal planner (sel 0.624 at N_p = 40),
 468:    the crossover sits at β\* ≈ 0.30 — inside the predicted band; below
 469:    β = 0.10 distributed selection remains superior everywhere. Against
 470:    the 15%-bandwidth planner no crossover exists at any tested β.
 471: 5. **Prediction 5 (visibility gap survives at 8-15 points) HELD in
 472:    direction, exceeded in size.** The calibrated status quo still
 473:    overstates real delivery by ~19 points: with p = 0.35, two-thirds of
 474:    diverted milestones remain officially recorded as complete. "Formally
 475:    controlled, still misreported" is now a number too.

